bio.info:
A man with three spirits of separate identity, mind, and control. 3'9 in height. likes to explore on his own. Prefers to be alone, he feels his identities can hurt. Guilty for things out of control, but with great cover up, as a __trick__, hence 'Sutela'. Likely to hide emotions, yet ends up being like a magnet for people (relevant in the future).

[Reference Sheet if you so desire](https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/763858632319434792/913526893607792660/proper_ref_sheet.png)
bio.backstory:
He was born with multi-spirituality, from weakness. __The Ascended__, finally born. It was a secret kept to his parents. He was forced to not reveal the secret. Yet he gathered friends with it. But at 16, it was revealed, ~~from rumors~~.

```The Ascended, from Mythology of Ventrah: someone on an illegal state of ascension, growing in spiritual force. Never meant to exist, met with hatred.
Maturity, harmony, and confidence, grants them infinitude.``` 

Ventrah locals were ready for a hunt, by greed, and is still active. He had to run away. (Yaretza - dimensional travel).

bio.\"a:
A man of three identities, with the ability of changing between them, on accident. Tho they're pretty subtle right now, they can strengthen in a way or another. 3'9 in height, a guy that likes to explore on his own, or not try and spend time with the group. He prefers to be alone because of identity issues and how he believes it can hurt other people. A man of regrets, feeling guilty for a lot of things, but with great ways to cover that up, as a trick, hence 'Sutela'. A stoic, distant person with trust issues, hence why he likes to leave groups whenever he feels like it.

EDIT: As of now he is getting a lot better with himself. He still hides stuff but he is going to be a lot more open about it.

bio.info: A cheerful but somewhat egotistical Tanuki. He wears a slightly loose, blue short-sleeved turtleneck to match his Brown fur with dark tan cargo shorts, and a utility belt where he keeps his shortsword around his waist. He may resemble Valoria in many ways, both being Tanukis, but Sky's tail is slightly larger, as well as being a bit fluffier. He seems to have an empty look in his eyes, though it's hard to discern.
bio.backstory: Sky's hometown was burned down to the ground by a faction that wanted to destroy the world. After Sky fled the smoldering ashes of (what was left of) his village, he decided to travel the world in order to find the people that did this. This eventually led to him becoming an adventurer, and by proxy, learning swordsmanship. As a Tanuki, it was easy for him to learn it at first, however even he needed some kind of example. After a long while and plenty of hard work, he became what's known as a veteran adventurer, and one of the youngest ones at that time, and even now. But even with all of this, he still could not find the culprits that burned down his village. To this day he is still investigating and researching on the ones responsible for destroying the place he called home.

He had a simple life going through, helping out in need, but the life simply could not last for so long, despite it going for over 500 years. The reason why Wish managed to end up in ``[Insert Planet Here]`` is unknown. Many people over there speculate that as the connection of upper forces, which are defined in the ``Mythology of Ventrah``.
